freetext.SYMPTOMS_DESCRIPTION: Excrutiating and Severe low back pain,  still,  on and off.  Trouble sleeping, really bad, like never before!!!

freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: Body aches on the left side of my body,  arm, back,  hip,  thigh,  and leg ask the way to the ankle. I had that last time also,  but it started on day 4-5 and lasted about 7 days.  I got that same pain today,  on day 1 of 2nd vaccine.
Low back aching x 2 days,  and a slight dripping nose. NOT sure if it's related to the vaccine or the crazy weather here because I do have arthritis and it has been raining, windy, and cold outside.
My arm is a little sore around the injection site,  nothing major really.

Pain in my left sciatic radiating down to my ankle.  May be the cold windy weather, or something else besides the vaccine,  but I thought I would mention it because the pain is bad enough that I had to take a pain pill last night and put a heating pad on the area.
Still have a dripping nose and a little stopped up that I have had from day 1 of the vaccine.
